Package banana.positionallist

Interface PositionalList<E>

Type Parameters:
E - type of element contained by Positions in the list
All Known Implementing Classes:
LinkedPositionalList
public interface PositionalList<E>
Interface for PositionalList ADT. A positional list is a collection of Positions each of which stores an element.
Since:
1.0
Author:
Gilbert Ssenyonjo
See Also:
Position

    Modifier and Type Method Description
    Position<E> addAfter​(Position<E> p, E e)
    Inserts element e immediately after Position p and produces Position of e.
    Position<E> addBefore​(Position<E> p, E e)
    Inserts element e immediately after Position p and produces Position of e.
    Position<E> addFirst​(E e)
    Inserts element e to the start of the list and produces its new Position.
    Position<E> addLast​(E e)
    Inserts element e to the end of the list and produces its new Position.
    Position<E> after​(Position<E> p)
    Produces the Position immediately after Position p or null if p is the last Position in the list.
    Position<E> before​(Position<E> p)
    Produces the Position immediately before Position p or null if p is the first Position in the list.
    Position<E> first()
    Produces the first Position in the list or null if the list is empty.
    boolean isEmpty()
    Produces true if the list has no Positions.
    Position<E> last()
    Produces the last Position in the list or null if the list is empty.
    java.lang.Iterable<Position<E>> positions()
    Produces an iterable of the list's Positions.
    E remove​(Position<E> p)
    Removes Position p from the list and produces the element stored at Position p.
    E set​(Position<E> p, E e)
    Replaces the element stored at Position p and produces the replaced element.
    int size()
    Produces the number of Positions in the list.

    • remove

      E remove​(Position<E> p)
      Removes Position p from the list and produces the element stored at Position p.

      Once Position p has been removed from the list, p is invalidated to make it unusable in other operations/methods on the list.

      Parameters:
      p - Position to be removed from the list.
      Throws:
      InvalidPosition - if Position p does not belong to this list.
